00339     /* rdhwr $31 is the 64 bit cmvcount register, it needs to be split
00340        into one or two (depending on the width of the result) properly
00341        sign extended registers.  All other registers are 32 bits wide
00342        and already properly sign extended. */
00343 #define CVMX_RDHWRX(result, regstr, ASM_STMT) ({            \
00344   if (regstr == 31) {                           \
00345     if (sizeof(result) == 8) {                      \
00346       ASM_STMT (".set\tpush\n"                      \
00347         "\t.set\tmips64r2\n"                    \
00348         "\trdhwr\t%L0,$31\n"                    \
00349         "\tdsra\t%M0,%L0,32\n"                  \
00350         "\tsll\t%L0,%L0,0\n"                    \
00351         "\t.set\tpop": "=d"(result));               \
00352     } else {                                \
00353       unsigned long _v;                         \
00354       ASM_STMT ("rdhwr\t%0,$31\n"                   \
00355         "\tsll\t%0,%0,0" : "=d"(_v));               \
00356       result = (typeof(result))_v;                  \
00357     }                                   \
00358   } else {                              \
00359     unsigned long _v;                           \
00360     ASM_STMT ("rdhwr\t%0,$" CVMX_TMP_STR(regstr) : "=d"(_v));       \
00361     result = (typeof(result))_v;                    \
00362   }})
